evon, England":"英國英格蘭戴文","lifeSummary":"當William Walker於1350年出生在英國英格蘭戴文時，他的父親Simon Walker25歲，母親Wife Walker25歲。他和Isabella Walker至少有2個兒子。他去世在英國英格蘭維爾爾。"},"zh-hans":{"1350–":"1350年–殁","1350–Male":"1350年–殁","1355–Female":"1355年–殁","1409–1475":"1409年–1475年","1440–1516":"1440年–1516年","1325–Male":"1325年–殁","1325–Female":"1325年–殁","1325":"1325年","1355":"1355年","1475":"1475年","1440":"1440年","1350":"1350年","1409":"1409年","1516":"1516年","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"英国貝德福爾斯特亞特利 煙雨 沙","Wiltshire, England":"英国英格兰維爾爾","England":"英国","Devon, England":"英国英格兰戴文","lifeSummary":"当William Walker于1350年出生在英国英格兰戴文时，他的父亲Simon Walker25岁，母亲Wife Walker25岁。他和Isabella Walker至少有2个儿子。他去世在英国英格兰維爾爾。"},"hr":{"1350–":"1350.–preminuo","1350–Male":"1350.–preminuo","1355–Female":"1355–preminula","1409–1475":"1409.–1475","1440–1516":"1440.–1516","1325–Male":"1325–preminuo","1325–Female":"1325–preminula","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440.","1350":"1350.","1409":"1409.","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1350–":"1350–Zesnulý","1350–Male":"1350–Zesnulý","1355–Female":"1355–Zesnulá","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Zesnulý","1325–Female":"1325–Zesnulá","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, Anglie","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","England":"Anglie","Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1350–":"1350–Afdød","1350–Male":"1350–Afdød","1355–Female":"1355–Afdød","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Afdød","1325–Female":"1325–Afdød","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1350–":"1350–Overleden","1350–Male":"1350–Overleden","1355–Female":"1355–Overleden","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Overleden","1325–Female":"1325–Overleden","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1350–":"1350–Deceased","1350–Male":"1350–Deceased","1355–Female":"1355–Deceased","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Deceased","1325–Female":"1325–Deceased","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walker","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (mainly North and Midlands) and Scottish: occupational name for a fuller, from Middle English <i>walker</i>, Old English <i>wealcere</i> (an agent derivative of <i>wealcan</i> ‘to walk, tread’), ‘one who trampled cloth in a bath of lye or kneaded it, in order to strengthen it’. This was the regular term for the occupation during the Middle Ages in western and northern England. Compare   Fuller   and   Tucker  . As a Scottish surname it has also been used as a translation of Gaelic <b>Mac an Fhucadair</b> ‘son of the fuller’. This surname is also very common among African Americans.","History: The name was brought to North America from northern England and Scotland independently by many different bearers in the 17th and 18th centuries. Samuel Walker came to Lynn, MA, <i>c.</i> 1630; Philip Walker was in Rehoboth, MA, in or before 1643. The surname was also established in VA before 1650; a Thomas Walker, born in 1715 in King and Queen County, VA, was a physician, soldier, and explorer."],"variants":[{"name":"Walcher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gunther, Hans, Horst, Klaus.","German: variant of   Walker   or   Walch  ."]},{"name":"Waker","meanings":["English (Yorkshire):","either a nickname for a watchful person or an occupational name for a watchman, from Middle English <i>waker</i> ‘watchful, vigilant’ (Old English <i>wacor</i>) and the derived noun.","mostly an early Modern English and Scots variant of   Walker  ."]},{"name":"Fuller","meanings":["English: occupational name for a dresser of cloth, from Middle English <i>fuller</i> ‘fuller of cloth’ (partly from Old English <i>fullere</i>, partly from Old French <i>fouleor</i>, <i>foleur</i>, Latin <i>fullo</i>). Raw cloth had to be fulled, i.e. scoured, cleansed, and thickened by beating or trampling it in water, a process also known as <i>walking</i> or <i>tucking</i>, hence the surnames   Walker   and   Tucker   alongside <i>Fuller</i>. These three terms and surnames are characteristic of different parts of England. In general, in Middle English, <i>Fuller</i> is southern and eastern, while <i>Walker</i> belongs to the west and north and <i>Tucker</i> is southwestern. Compare   Fullen  .","English: variant of   Fullard   with loss of <i>-d</i>.","German (<b>Füller</b>): occupational name for a person whose work involved filling, such as a dauber, or a nickname for a gourmand or glutton. Compare   Filler  ."]},{"name":"Walke","meanings":["German: metonymic occupational name for a fuller, from Middle High German <i>walke</i> ‘fulling mill’. Compare   Walker  .","English (Devon): variant of   Walk  ."]},{"name":"Walck","meanings":["German: variant of   Walker   or   Walch  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Walker was born in 1350, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Simon Walker, was 25 and his mother, Wife Walker, was 25. He had at least 2 sons with Isabella Walker. He died in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1350–":"1350–Surnud","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1350–":"1350–Kuollut","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1350–":"1350–Décédé","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Décédé","1325–Female":"1325–Décédée","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, Angleterre","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Walker est né en 1350, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Simon Walker, avait 25 ans et sa mère, Wife Walker, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 2 fils avec Isabella Walker. Il est décédé à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1350–":"1350–Verstorben","1350–Male":"1350–Verstorben","1355–Female":"1355–Verstorben","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Verstorben","1325–Female":"1325–Verstorben","1325":"1325","1355":"1355","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","1350":"1350","1409":"1409","1516":"1516","Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Streatley with Sharpenhoe, Bedfordshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als William Walker 1350 in Devon, England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war sein Vater Simon Walker 25 und seine Mutter Wife Walker 25. Er hatte mit Isabella Walker mindestens 2 Söhne. Er starb in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1350–":"1350–Desede","1350–Male":"1350–Desede","1355–Female":"1355–Desede","1409–1475":"1409–1475","1440–1516":"1440–1516","1325–Male":"1325–Desede","1325–Female":"1325–Desede","13